   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER SIX THE DEFINITION OF OUR SPIRIT Scripture Reading: 1 Thes 5:23; Heb 4:12b; Gen 2:7; Zech 12:1b; Isa 42:5; Luke 9:23-25; Job 32:8; Prov 20:27; John 4:24; 2 Tim 4:22a; Gen 2:9b; 1:27; 1 Cor 6:17; Rom 9:1; 8:16; 1:9; Luke 1:47; 1 Cor 2:11; Mark 2:8 OUTLINE We being created by God a tripartite being 1 Thes 5:23; Heb 4:12b: With a body formed of the dust, as our outward frame Gen 2:7a.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>With a spirit produced of God's breath, as our intrinsic organ, ranked with the heavens and the earth Gen 2:7b; Zech 12:1b; Isa 42:5.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>With a soul, the issue of our spirit being added to our body, as our self in between our body and our spirit Gen 2:7c; Luke 9:23-25.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Our spirit being particularly created by God as our particular organ Gen 2:7b: With the breath of God Job 32:8.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>As the lamp of Jehovah Prov 20:27.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>For us to worship God to contact and contain God John 4:24; 2 Tim 4:22a.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>For us to receive God as life and to express God Gen 2:9b; 1:27.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>For us to be joined to God as one spirit 1 Cor 6:17.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>The composition of our spirit: The conscience Rom 9:1; cf.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Rom 8:16.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The fellowship John 4:24; Rom 1:9; Luke 1:47.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>The intuition 1 Cor 2:11; Mark 2:8.</S>
   </TEXT>
